trashday

Class TrashDaySpeechletRequestStreamHandlerTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • trashday.storage.DynamoAccessTestHelpers
      • trashday.TrashDaySpeechletRequestStreamHandlerTest

  • public class TrashDaySpeechletRequestStreamHandlerTest
extends DynamoAccessTestHelpers
    JUnit tests that work by providing input that emulates the JSON-based requests produced by the Alexa service when users talk to our skill.

    Most tests work by creating test input in a TestDataRequest object and expected test output in a TestDataAskResponse object. The test input is given to our skill's handler function. The resulting JSON output from the handler is then parsed, formatted, and compared to the expected test output to determine if the test is successful.

    The remaining (non-Test) functions in the class focus on producing test input data and maintaining a uniform state of the Dynamo DB database between each test.

    Author:
    J. Todd Baldwin
    See Also:
    JsonUnit

        public List<TestDataUtterance> createDialogNewSchedule()
        Create a list of the user commands needed to create a new Schedule. JUnit test functions can feed this list to the runDialog method as part of a test.

        Test Utterances:

        • SetTimeZoneIntent set time zone to {TimeZone}
        • AddPickupIntent add {PickupName} pickup on {DayOfWeek} at {TimeOfDay}
        • AddPickupIntent add {PickupName} pickup at {TimeOfDay} on {DayOfWeek}
        Returns:
        List of TestDataUtterance objects suitable for the runDialog method.

      • runDialog

        public TestDataGeneralResponse runDialog(List<TestDataUtterance> dialog,
                                         TestDataGeneralResponse startingResponse)
                                  throws IOException
        Run a list of user commands (TestDataUtterance objects) through the skill handler. Carries sessionAttribute date beteween the tests.
        Parameters:
        dialog - List of TestDataUtterances
        startingResponse - TestDataGeneralResponse from any prior test performed. Used to seed sessionAttributes, if they exist.
        Returns:
        TestDataGeneralResponse representing the last response received from running all the commands in the dialog.
        Throws:
        IOException - if the handler has IO problems.

        public static <T> Stream<List<T>> getCombinationsStream(List<T> list)
        Find all combinations of a list's items. Credit to Adrian Leonhard

        Example Usage: slotCombos = getCombinationsStream(slots).collect(Collectors.toList());

        Type Parameters:
        T - This is the type parameter
        Parameters:
        list - find all combinations of these items
        Returns:
        Stream containing all the combination lists.
